originalText.text: The doctor who saw me was terrible. At baseline, he had absolutely no bedside manner whatsoever. Next, he ordered an x ray and I mentioned I did not think there were any bone issues with my arm (I was assaulted by way of punch to my arm a few nights prior). This was confirmed by the x rays which is fine. However I asked whether it could be nerve damage and was referred to an orthopedic surgeon. When I asked what could be done if it is nerve damage, the doctor was wholly unhelpful. He said sometimes it just heals, maybe physical therapy. I asked how long I should wait to see if the pain subsides before seeing the referral. He again provided no appropriate response, merely staying 1 week, 2 weeks, maybe 3. I had also gone in for a persistent cough that I’d had for about 5 weeks. I said I was worried it might be bronchitis and asked whether we could do or check anything. He said if it’s getting better, then it’s no big deal and that it’s just “human.” That is an absurd thing to tell a patient who’s come in concerned about chest, mucus filled coughs that have been there for 5 weeks. That this immediately followed the ridiculous assessment of my assault injury made it more infuriating. This was a complete waste of my time and money. However, the PA Steven (sp?) was incredibly nice, and made me feel comfortable. Unfortunately, that was followed by an unpleasant experience with the doctor.

originalText.text: I have consistently had A+ experiences at this location.  Front desk is courteous and efficient.  Each time I’ve visited the medical assistants were kind and thorough.  I’ve had excellent experiences with the physicians and most recently the physician assistant who treated me.  Medical staff were very professional.

originalText.text: The worst experience ever. I came with the glass in my foot and they did not even clean the wound. I was told to make an x-ray within 48h- when I came to the clinic they told me that first I need to be checked once again by the doctor that will advise if I should have an x-ray, even though I came within 48h. The waitlist for the doctor appointment was 1h and I did not get the x-ray. The receptionist was very rude and they did not listen to me at all. I would never recommend this clinic.

originalText.text: Went in because I have a painful UTI. The experience in the facility was courteous and professional, I was prescribed a drug that caused an allergic reaction. Tried to get the ‘Sensitivity’ results of the organism so my own doctor could prescribe the right medication. Still waiting and it is 4 days. Calls for ‘AfterCare’ information seem to go to a call center in India or another 3rd world country were English is poorly spoken. Still waiting for the full report.
